class Solution {
    public String greatestLetter(String s) {
        boolean[] lower = new boolean[26];
        boolean[] upper = new boolean[26];
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (Character.isLowerCase(c)) {
                lower[c - 'a'] = true;
            } else {
                upper[c - 'A'] = true;
            }
        }
        for (int i = 25; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (lower[i] && upper[i]) {
                return String.valueOf((char) ('A' + i));
            }
        }
        return "";
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once to track the occurrence of lowercase and uppercase letters, then iterates through the alphabet in reverse order to find the greatest letter that appears in both cases. It uses a constant amount of space to store the boolean arrays. 
